  "title": "Junior Operations Analyst (Global Markets / Derivatives)",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><ul><li>Adecco is partnering with a leading bank to look for a Operations Analyst in Global Financial Markets Team</li><li>Starts off as 1 year contract with high chance for extension/conversion</li><li><strong>Located at Changi Business Park</strong></li></ul><p><strong>The Job</strong><br />1. Provide settlement support to T&M on the Derivatives markets<br />2. Validation of Structured Notes products against source documents<br />3. Perform Position and other form of Reconciliation<br />4. UAT Testing<br /></p><ul><li>Exposure to global derivative products</li><li>Trade lifecycle knowledge</li><li>Position & reconciliation handling</li><li>Understanding of structured products</li><li>Hands‑on experience supporting a Global Markets desk</li></ul><p><br /><strong>The Talent</strong></p><ul><li>Prior banking internships are an advantage but not mandatory. Training will be provided in Global Markets operations (Derivatives & Structured Products).</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and Excel</li></ul><p><strong>Next Steps</strong></p><ul><li>Drop your resume and contact us to follow-up, or send your resume to <strong>amos.tan@adecco.com</strong></li><li>Email Topic: Apply Operations Analyst</li><li>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted</li></ul><p>Amos Tan Jun Han</p><p>EA Licence Number: 91C2918</p><p>Personnel Registration Number: R23113385</p>",
